WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
and looking forward to what God has for us this evening.

00:00:03.500 --> 00:00:07.000
And, of course, over the last couple of Wednesday nights,

00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:09.000
kind of entering into 2026,

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:14.500
we've had this thought, a longing to see God work.

00:00:14.500 --> 00:00:16.500
And I've asked this question,

00:00:16.500 --> 00:00:19.000
and I'd like for you to consider it this evening

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:21.500
by way of introduction.

00:00:21.500 --> 00:00:23.500
Is God working in your life?

00:00:23.500 --> 00:00:25.000
And you've been to think about that.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:27.000
Is there any evidence, is there something that you can see

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:29.000
how God is working in your life?

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:30.500
How is God growing you?

00:00:30.500 --> 00:00:32.000
What is God teaching you?

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:34.000
What is He teaching you about Himself?

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:36.000
What's He teaching you about you?

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:38.000
And what's He teaching you from His Word?

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:40.000
And you just begin to see how God is working.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:43.500
How is God using you in the lives of others?

00:00:43.500 --> 00:00:46.500
We're to invest, intentionally invest in others,

00:00:46.500 --> 00:00:50.000
and God will use us to be able to share the gospel with folks.

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:52.000
God will use us to be able to encourage folks.

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:55.000
God will use us to be able to disciple folks.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:00:57.500
And just begin to think about how God is working.

00:00:57.500 --> 00:00:59.000
And really as we examine our lives,

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:00.500
and we have this idea, this thought,

00:01:00.500 --> 00:01:02.500
a longing to see God work,

00:01:02.500 --> 00:01:05.500
I've said this each of the last two Wednesday evenings,

00:01:05.500 --> 00:01:08.500
I desire to see God work in my life personally.

00:01:08.500 --> 00:01:10.500
I desire to see God work in your life.

00:01:10.500 --> 00:01:13.500
I desire to see God work in our church corporately.

00:01:13.500 --> 00:01:18.500
That God would use us to make a difference in this region

00:01:18.500 --> 00:01:21.500
where He has placed us in Northern Virginia.

00:01:21.500 --> 00:01:24.000
And you see all the things that are going on in our world,

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
and I believe that it's obvious that the Lord is coming soon,

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:30.000
and we look forward to that.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:32.000
And the days are short.

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:34.000
There's much work to be accomplished.

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:38.000
There's a world that needs to hear the gospel of the Lord Jesus Christ,

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:43.000
and we desperately need to see Him do what only He can do.

00:01:43.000 --> 00:01:46.000
And I want to remind you, we said this last week,

00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:52.000
but I want to remind you that God has as much power today as He ever has.

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:55.000
Amen? He has as much power today as He ever has.

00:01:55.000 --> 00:01:58.000
When He created the universe, He didn't lose any of His power.

00:01:58.000 --> 00:02:01.000
When He parted the Red Sea, He didn't lose any of His power.

00:02:01.000 --> 00:02:03.000
When He provided manna for all those...

00:02:03.000 --> 00:02:05.000
He doesn't lose any of His power.

00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:07.000
He has all power. He is able.

00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:10.000
And last week, we looked at a portion of Scripture

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:12.000
in which the kings were gathered,

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:16.000
and we looked at Jehoram and Jehoshaphat and that agreement that was made,

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:20.000
and how they went to Elisha, and Elisha delivered that message

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:25.000
and of digging the trenches and the pits,

00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:27.000
and that God would give water.

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:30.000
And he said this, it was a light thing. It was a light thing.

00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:34.000
And we kind of focused on that for a few minutes last Wednesday evening

00:02:34.000 --> 00:02:37.000
and talking about the idea that it's no big deal for God.

00:02:37.000 --> 00:02:39.000
It was a light thing.

00:02:39.000 --> 00:02:42.000
And he said, furthermore, God was also going to give them victory

00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:47.000
there in that endeavor that they were seeking to have victory.

00:02:47.000 --> 00:02:49.000
As we come to this thought this evening,

00:02:49.000 --> 00:02:51.000
we're in 2 Kings chapter number 20,

00:02:51.000 --> 00:02:53.000
and we find that this portion of Scripture

00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:57.000
begins with an announcement regarding King Hezekiah.

00:02:57.000 --> 00:03:00.000
Now, before I get into the text,

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:02.000
let me just remind you that Hezekiah,

00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:04.000
like Jehoshaphat last week,

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:07.000
we talked about him being basically a good king.

00:03:07.000 --> 00:03:10.000
Hezekiah is a king in Judah, and he's a good king.

00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:13.000
And we will see, if you were to study through his life

00:03:13.000 --> 00:03:16.000
beyond the chapter here,

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:19.000
that unfortunately he was given 15 additional years,

00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:23.000
and he really didn't use those the best way that he could use those.

00:03:23.000 --> 00:03:26.000
But we do find that he was basically a good king.

00:03:26.000 --> 00:03:28.000
He was a man that trusted the Lord.

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:31.000
And you think about Rabshakeh and Sennacherib,

00:03:31.000 --> 00:03:34.000
the king of Assyria,

00:03:34.000 --> 00:03:37.000
and how they came against Israel and would take Israel captive.

00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:39.000
And they came against Judah,

00:03:39.000 --> 00:03:42.000
and Rabshakeh as the general would come

00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:44.000
and make all of these threats.

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:47.000
And Hezekiah trusted the Lord, and Hezekiah prayed,

00:03:47.000 --> 00:03:49.000
and Hezekiah believed that God was able,

00:03:49.000 --> 00:03:52.000
and God delivered, and God gave victory,

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:54.000
and God defeated the Assyrians.

00:03:54.000 --> 00:03:57.000
And we see that Hezekiah had experienced,

00:03:57.000 --> 00:04:01.000
had lived through seeing God work and do great things.

00:04:01.000 --> 00:04:04.000
We come here to 2 Kings 20,

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:06.000
and God will use the prophet Isaiah

00:04:06.000 --> 00:04:09.000
to deliver a message to Hezekiah.

00:04:09.000 --> 00:04:11.000
Notice in verse 1 it says,

00:04:11.000 --> 00:04:14.000
This was Hezekiah sick unto death.

00:04:14.000 --> 00:04:17.000
And the prophet Isaiah, the son of Amos,

00:04:17.000 --> 00:04:19.000
came to him and said unto him,

00:04:19.000 --> 00:04:23.000
Thus saith the Lord. Notice this.

00:04:23.000 --> 00:04:26.000
Set thine house in order,

00:04:26.000 --> 00:04:31.000
for thou shalt die and not live.

00:04:31.000 --> 00:04:34.000
That will wake you up. Amen?

00:04:34.000 --> 00:04:37.000
I mean, this is an announcement that the Bible says,

00:04:37.000 --> 00:04:39.000
that Isaiah says, Thus saith the Lord.

00:04:39.000 --> 00:04:42.000
And this announcement, this is given

00:04:42.000 --> 00:04:44.000
with regard to Hezekiah.

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:47.000
He was sick, and God says through the prophet,

00:04:47.000 --> 00:04:49.000
Set thine house in order,

00:04:49.000 --> 00:04:53.000
for thou shalt die and not live.

00:04:53.000 --> 00:04:55.000
The reality, it's not the main focus

00:04:55.000 --> 00:04:57.000
of the message this evening,

00:04:57.000 --> 00:05:00.000
but the reality is that for every one of us,

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:03.000
at some point we're going to face death.

00:05:03.000 --> 00:05:06.000
We obviously pray and hope that the Lord

00:05:06.000 --> 00:05:08.000
would return during our lifetime

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:10.000
and what a blessing it would be

00:05:10.000 --> 00:05:12.000
to be raptured out of here.

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:17.000
But the reality is that the time of God's return,

00:05:17.000 --> 00:05:20.000
the rapture, is unknown and it's imminent.

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:22.000
I believe it could happen at any moment,

00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:24.000
but we don't know when it's going to be.

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:26.000
But we know that it's appointed

00:05:26.000 --> 00:05:28.000
unto man once to die.

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:30.000
And the reality is that death is not

00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:32.000
the worst thing that could happen to us

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:34.000
because to be absent from the body

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:36.000
is to be present with the Lord.

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:37.000
When you think about where it says

00:05:37.000 --> 00:05:38.000
set thine house in order,

00:05:38.000 --> 00:05:40.000
obviously there were things that

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:42.000
when someone dies, there's oftentimes

00:05:42.000 --> 00:05:44.000
relatives and various things

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:46.000
that need to be set in order.

00:05:46.000 --> 00:05:49.000
And so this would obviously wake up Hezekiah.

00:05:49.000 --> 00:05:51.000
It would be an announcement

00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:53.000
that would be quite impactful.

00:05:53.000 --> 00:05:55.000
If somebody came to you, not a physician,

00:05:55.000 --> 00:05:57.000
but if the Lord, this is God speaking

00:05:57.000 --> 00:05:59.000
through the prophet, you're going to die.

00:05:59.000 --> 00:06:05.000
And that's a sobering reality for Hezekiah.

00:06:05.000 --> 00:06:06.000
But I want you to notice that as we look

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:08.000
through this portion of Scripture

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:10.000
and again a longing to see God work,

00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:12.000
we notice some things about Hezekiah

00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:14.000
and about the Lord in these next

00:06:14.000 --> 00:06:16.000
several verses that are noteworthy

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:17.000
and I hope that they would help us

00:06:17.000 --> 00:06:19.000
this evening to encourage us

00:06:19.000 --> 00:06:20.000
and also to challenge us.

00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:22.000
I want you to notice first of all with me

00:06:22.000 --> 00:06:24.000
Hezekiah's prayer.

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:26.000
Notice in verses two through four,

00:06:26.000 --> 00:06:28.000
God gives to us the record

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:29.000
of Hezekiah's prayer.

00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:32.000
He receives this word from Isaiah

00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:34.000
in verse number one and it seems

00:06:34.000 --> 00:06:37.000
as if this happens very quickly,

00:06:37.000 --> 00:06:39.000
immediate succession if you will,

00:06:39.000 --> 00:06:40.000
that in verse number two it says,

00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:43.000
then he turned, that's Hezekiah,

00:06:43.000 --> 00:06:46.000
then he turned his face to the wall

00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:49.000
and prayed unto the Lord saying,

00:06:49.000 --> 00:06:52.000
I beseech thee, O Lord, remember now

00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:54.000
how I have walked before thee in truth

00:06:54.000 --> 00:06:56.000
and with a perfect heart

00:06:56.000 --> 00:06:58.000
and have done that which is good

00:06:58.000 --> 00:06:59.000
in thy sight.

00:06:59.000 --> 00:07:02.000
And Hezekiah wept sore

00:07:02.000 --> 00:07:04.000
and it came to pass after Isaiah

00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:06.000
was gone out into the middle court

00:07:06.000 --> 00:07:08.000
that the word of the Lord came to him saying

00:07:08.000 --> 00:07:09.000
and we'll pick up in verse five

00:07:09.000 --> 00:07:10.000
in just a moment,

00:07:10.000 --> 00:07:12.000
but I want you to notice

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:14.000
as we consider Hezekiah's prayer

00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:18.000
some things about this response if you will

00:07:18.000 --> 00:07:20.000
and I would say this, number one,

00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:22.000
Hezekiah prayed immediately.

00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:24.000
He prayed immediately.

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:26.000
The Bible says, set thine house in order

00:07:26.000 --> 00:07:28.000
for thou shalt die and not live.

00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:30.000
Then he turned his face to the wall

00:07:30.000 --> 00:07:32.000
and prayed unto the Lord saying.

00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:35.000
And when I think about this prayer of Hezekiah

00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:38.000
and I think about the truth that he prayed immediately,

00:07:38.000 --> 00:07:40.000
you know God wants us to be people of prayer.

00:07:40.000 --> 00:07:43.000
He wants prayer to be our first response,

00:07:43.000 --> 00:07:44.000
not a last resort.

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:48.000
He wants us to be characterized as people of prayer

00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:50.000
and as we begin to examine our own prayer lives,

00:07:50.000 --> 00:07:52.000
we begin to examine our lives

00:07:52.000 --> 00:07:55.000
and consider the various things that we face

00:07:55.000 --> 00:07:56.000
and we deal with in life,

00:07:56.000 --> 00:07:59.000
the question is do we respond immediately

00:07:59.000 --> 00:08:00.000
in prayer?

00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:02.000
Do we seek the face of God?

00:08:02.000 --> 00:08:04.000
Do we come before the Lord?

00:08:04.000 --> 00:08:06.000
It's a great privilege that we have

00:08:06.000 --> 00:08:08.000
to go directly to the throne of God,

00:08:08.000 --> 00:08:10.000
that we can have that boldness.

00:08:10.000 --> 00:08:12.000
I preached about it on Sunday morning

00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:15.000
with regard to that promise in James 1

00:08:15.000 --> 00:08:16.000
in verse number five.

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:19.000
If any of you lack wisdom, let them ask of God

00:08:19.000 --> 00:08:21.000
and the fact that we have that privilege,

00:08:21.000 --> 00:08:24.000
that freedom, that opportunity

00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:27.000
that we can go directly before the throne of God

00:08:27.000 --> 00:08:29.000
and we can seek his face

00:08:29.000 --> 00:08:32.000
and it's a great privilege for us.

00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:34.000
I said this on Sunday morning

00:08:34.000 --> 00:08:36.000
and I believe it's worth repeating

00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:38.000
with regard to this portion of scripture

00:08:38.000 --> 00:08:41.000
and I said this, it doesn't trouble God

00:08:41.000 --> 00:08:44.000
when we ask him for wisdom.

00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:48.000
As the context of the message on Sunday morning

00:08:48.000 --> 00:08:51.000
from James 1 in verses five through eight,

00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:53.000
it doesn't trouble God.

00:08:53.000 --> 00:08:56.000
When you pray, when I pray, we're not troubling God.

00:08:57.000 --> 00:08:59.000
And I said this, what really troubles God

00:08:59.000 --> 00:09:01.000
is when we don't pray.

00:09:02.000 --> 00:09:07.000
Because we fail to see what God is able to do

00:09:07.000 --> 00:09:10.000
and we find this evening that our God is able

00:09:10.000 --> 00:09:12.000
and we find here this evening

00:09:12.000 --> 00:09:14.000
that he prayed immediately.

00:09:14.000 --> 00:09:15.000
Not only did he pray immediately,

00:09:15.000 --> 00:09:17.000
but it would seem as you look at verse number three,

00:09:17.000 --> 00:09:18.000
the latter part of the verse,

00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:20.000
it says, and Hezekiah wept sore.

00:09:20.000 --> 00:09:22.000
I would say this, not only he prayed immediately,

00:09:22.000 --> 00:09:24.000
but he prayed fervently

00:09:24.000 --> 00:09:26.000
and I think about the truth in James five

00:09:26.000 --> 00:09:29.000
that the effectual fervent prayer

00:09:29.000 --> 00:09:31.000
of a righteous man availeth much

00:09:31.000 --> 00:09:34.000
and you begin to think about this fervent prayer

00:09:34.000 --> 00:09:36.000
and Hezekiah, he wept sore.

00:09:36.000 --> 00:09:39.000
He speaks before the Lord with regard to his testimony

00:09:39.000 --> 00:09:41.000
with his walk before the Lord

00:09:41.000 --> 00:09:44.000
and his behavior and praise the Lord

00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:46.000
that he had that kind of a testimony,

00:09:46.000 --> 00:09:48.000
that he was a man that did walk with the Lord,

00:09:48.000 --> 00:09:50.000
but we find that he prays immediately

00:09:50.000 --> 00:09:52.000
and he prays fervently

00:09:52.000 --> 00:09:55.000
and prayer ought to be our first response

00:09:55.000 --> 00:09:57.000
and I wonder this evening,

00:09:57.000 --> 00:09:59.000
sometimes as we consider this idea,

00:09:59.000 --> 00:10:00.000
we wanna see God.

00:10:00.000 --> 00:10:04.000
Well, God works as we pray, amen?

00:10:04.000 --> 00:10:09.000
And the reality is that God has ordained it in his word

00:10:09.000 --> 00:10:12.000
that his hand is moved by the prayers of his people.

00:10:12.000 --> 00:10:16.000
And so often you can read throughout the scriptures

00:10:16.000 --> 00:10:19.000
of God's people praying and what God does

00:10:19.000 --> 00:10:22.000
and how God shows his power.

00:10:22.000 --> 00:10:25.000
He delights in answering, he delights in demonstrating.

00:10:25.000 --> 00:10:28.000
I'll remind you in 2 Chronicles 7 in verse number 14,

00:10:29.000 --> 00:10:31.000
if my people, which are called by my name,

00:10:31.000 --> 00:10:34.000
shall humble themselves and what?

00:10:34.000 --> 00:10:38.000
And pray and seek my face and turn from their wicked ways,

00:10:38.000 --> 00:10:42.000
then will I hear from heaven and will forgive their sin

00:10:42.000 --> 00:10:44.000
and will heal their land.

00:10:44.000 --> 00:10:48.000
And we find that God gives the responsibility to his people

00:10:48.000 --> 00:10:51.000
to humble themselves, to pray, to seek his face,

00:10:51.000 --> 00:10:53.000
to turn from their wicked ways.

00:10:53.000 --> 00:10:57.000
And we see God's response to the prayer of his people.

00:10:57.000 --> 00:10:59.000
In fact, even within the context there,

00:10:59.000 --> 00:11:02.000
we find that Solomon had been dedicating

00:11:02.000 --> 00:11:04.000
through prayer to the temple

00:11:04.000 --> 00:11:06.000
and God says, I've heard your prayer.

00:11:06.000 --> 00:11:08.000
And what a blessing.

00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:10.000
And so we find this evening Hezekiah's prayer,

00:11:10.000 --> 00:11:12.000
but then we see God's promise.

00:11:12.000 --> 00:11:15.000
In verses five through seven, it's so precious.

00:11:15.000 --> 00:11:17.000
In verse four, it says, we read it a moment ago

00:11:17.000 --> 00:11:21.000
and it came to pass a fort Isaiah was gone out

00:11:21.000 --> 00:11:22.000
into the middle court.

00:11:22.000 --> 00:11:24.000
The word of the Lord came to him saying,

00:11:24.000 --> 00:11:26.000
and so if you can kind of in your mind's eye

00:11:26.000 --> 00:11:27.000
see what's happening.

00:11:27.000 --> 00:11:30.000
Isaiah enters in, he speaks to Hezekiah,

00:11:30.000 --> 00:11:33.000
gives him the announcement according to verse number one

00:11:33.000 --> 00:11:35.000
from the Lord, set thine house in order

00:11:35.000 --> 00:11:37.000
for thou shalt die and not live.

00:11:37.000 --> 00:11:39.000
And then Isaiah departs.

00:11:39.000 --> 00:11:40.000
He doesn't linger.

00:11:40.000 --> 00:11:41.000
He's not hanging around.

00:11:41.000 --> 00:11:42.000
He delivers the message.

00:11:42.000 --> 00:11:45.000
He departs and Hezekiah prays.

00:11:45.000 --> 00:11:49.000
And as Hezekiah is praying and as Isaiah is leaving,

00:11:49.000 --> 00:11:52.000
the Bible says a fort Isaiah was gone out

00:11:52.000 --> 00:11:54.000
into the middle court that the word of the Lord

00:11:54.000 --> 00:11:57.000
came to him saying, verse five, turn again.

00:11:57.000 --> 00:12:02.000
And so God is already answering the prayer of Hezekiah

00:12:02.000 --> 00:12:05.000
and God is giving a promise in these verses

00:12:05.000 --> 00:12:08.000
and he tells Isaiah to return back

00:12:08.000 --> 00:12:12.000
and to deliver the second message to Hezekiah.

00:12:12.000 --> 00:12:15.000
Notice, turn again and tell Hezekiah,

00:12:15.000 --> 00:12:17.000
the captain of my people.

00:12:17.000 --> 00:12:21.000
Thus saith the Lord, the God of David, thy father,

00:12:21.000 --> 00:12:24.000
I have heard thy prayer.

00:12:24.000 --> 00:12:26.000
I have seen thy tears.

00:12:26.000 --> 00:12:28.000
Behold, I will heal thee.

00:12:28.000 --> 00:12:30.000
On the third day thou shalt go up

00:12:30.000 --> 00:12:32.000
unto the house of the Lord and I will add

00:12:32.000 --> 00:12:35.000
unto thy days 15 years and I will deliver thee

00:12:35.000 --> 00:12:38.000
and this city out of the hand of the king of Assyria

00:12:38.000 --> 00:12:40.000
and I will defend this city for my own sake

00:12:40.000 --> 00:12:43.000
and for my servant David's sake.

00:12:43.000 --> 00:12:45.000
As we're gonna look at verses five and six

00:12:45.000 --> 00:12:47.000
and we'll look at verse seven here in just a moment,

00:12:47.000 --> 00:12:49.000
we think about God's promises here

00:12:49.000 --> 00:12:51.000
and I want you to be reminded of a couple

00:12:51.000 --> 00:12:54.000
of important truths that we find in verse number five.

00:12:54.000 --> 00:12:57.000
Number one is that God hears.

00:12:57.000 --> 00:12:58.000
God hears.

00:12:58.000 --> 00:13:02.000
He says this, I have heard thy prayer.

00:13:02.000 --> 00:13:04.000
I have heard thy prayer.

00:13:04.000 --> 00:13:05.000
We can ask ourselves the question,

00:13:05.000 --> 00:13:08.000
when's the last time God heard from us?

00:13:08.000 --> 00:13:10.000
You ever have some people that you don't hear from

00:13:10.000 --> 00:13:12.000
for a long time?

00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:14.000
Maybe you get that call on your phone

00:13:14.000 --> 00:13:15.000
and you're like, man, I haven't heard

00:13:15.000 --> 00:13:17.000
from this person for a long time.

00:13:17.000 --> 00:13:19.000
Maybe you say, I wonder what they want.

00:13:21.000 --> 00:13:24.000
I'm just trying to be relevant, help us understand.

00:13:24.000 --> 00:13:26.000
But the reality is that sometimes,

00:13:26.000 --> 00:13:29.000
when's the last time God heard from us?

00:13:29.000 --> 00:13:31.000
I mean in fervent prayer,

00:13:31.000 --> 00:13:34.000
that we're truly seeking the face of God

00:13:34.000 --> 00:13:39.000
and we find that God says, I have heard thy prayer.

00:13:39.000 --> 00:13:41.000
The psalmist talks about praying in the morning

00:13:41.000 --> 00:13:43.000
and the noon and the evening

00:13:43.000 --> 00:13:46.000
and coming before the presence of God

00:13:46.000 --> 00:13:48.000
and that God would hear his voice.

00:13:48.000 --> 00:13:50.000
And I would say to you this evening

00:13:50.000 --> 00:13:53.000
that God wants to commune with us.

00:13:53.000 --> 00:13:55.000
He wants us to be in his word.

00:13:55.000 --> 00:13:57.000
He wants us to pray.

00:13:57.000 --> 00:13:59.000
And you read in Ephesians 6 about

00:13:59.000 --> 00:14:00.000
putting on the whole armor of God,

00:14:00.000 --> 00:14:02.000
but then you get through that text

00:14:02.000 --> 00:14:03.000
and it talks about prayer

00:14:03.000 --> 00:14:06.000
and the importance of praying as God's people.

00:14:06.000 --> 00:14:08.000
And we understand that the enemy fights.

00:14:08.000 --> 00:14:10.000
I'm not sure in your life,

00:14:10.000 --> 00:14:12.000
but I know personally in my life,

00:14:12.000 --> 00:14:15.000
one of the biggest spiritual battles that I have

00:14:15.000 --> 00:14:18.000
every day is in the matter of prayer.

00:14:18.000 --> 00:14:20.000
Why does the enemy fight prayer so much?

00:14:20.000 --> 00:14:24.000
Because prayer is so effective and he fights prayer.

00:14:24.000 --> 00:14:28.000
And so we find that Isaiah returns to Hezekiah

00:14:28.000 --> 00:14:30.000
and he delivers a message from God

00:14:30.000 --> 00:14:32.000
that first I have heard thy prayer,

00:14:32.000 --> 00:14:33.000
that God hears us.

00:14:33.000 --> 00:14:37.000
But then he says this, I have seen thy tears.

00:14:37.000 --> 00:14:39.000
God sees us.

00:14:39.000 --> 00:14:43.000
He knows, he hears and he sees us.

00:14:44.000 --> 00:14:47.000
I begin to think about the truth

00:14:47.000 --> 00:14:51.000
of the interaction that Jesus had there

00:14:51.000 --> 00:14:53.000
during his earthly ministry and he's interacting

00:14:53.000 --> 00:14:55.000
and he's speaking about the way

00:14:55.000 --> 00:14:57.000
in which the religious leaders would pray

00:14:57.000 --> 00:14:59.000
and the way in which the religious leaders would fast

00:14:59.000 --> 00:15:01.000
and they would pray so that they could

00:15:01.000 --> 00:15:03.000
get the attention of everyone.

00:15:03.000 --> 00:15:05.000
And they would fast so that everyone would know,

00:15:05.000 --> 00:15:07.000
quote unquote, how spiritual they were

00:15:07.000 --> 00:15:08.000
and all of those things.

00:15:08.000 --> 00:15:10.000
And we find that the Lord Jesus Christ says,

00:15:10.000 --> 00:15:13.000
but when you pray, where did he tell them to go?

00:15:13.000 --> 00:15:16.000
He said, go into your closet, right?

00:15:16.000 --> 00:15:20.000
And he says that your father that seeth in secret

00:15:20.000 --> 00:15:23.000
shall reward thee openly.

00:15:23.000 --> 00:15:25.000
And I'm thankful this evening that we have

00:15:25.000 --> 00:15:28.000
the assurance that God hears our prayer,

00:15:28.000 --> 00:15:30.000
that God sees our tears.

00:15:30.000 --> 00:15:32.000
Listen, maybe you get before the Lord

00:15:32.000 --> 00:15:35.000
and you're just, I mean, you think about Hannah.

00:15:35.000 --> 00:15:38.000
I mean, she just poured her heart out before the Lord.

00:15:38.000 --> 00:15:41.000
I mean, sometimes we gotta have that

00:15:43.000 --> 00:15:45.000
tears flowing again.

00:15:45.000 --> 00:15:47.000
I preached a message several years ago

00:15:47.000 --> 00:15:50.000
about the man of God wept.

00:15:50.000 --> 00:15:52.000
And you begin to think about the prophet

00:15:52.000 --> 00:15:54.000
and the word that he heard with regard to

00:15:54.000 --> 00:15:57.000
what was going to happen and how it caused him to weep

00:15:57.000 --> 00:16:00.000
and I kind of talked about how we need to weep again.

00:16:00.000 --> 00:16:04.000
God sees our heart, he sees our tears,

00:16:04.000 --> 00:16:06.000
he hears us when we pray.

00:16:06.000 --> 00:16:09.000
And I want you to notice that not only does God hear

00:16:09.000 --> 00:16:11.000
and God see, but we find that God answers.

00:16:11.000 --> 00:16:13.000
And really that's the promise that we find here.

00:16:13.000 --> 00:16:15.000
There's two aspects of this promise

00:16:15.000 --> 00:16:18.000
that is given to us here that God delivers

00:16:18.000 --> 00:16:20.000
through the prophet Isaiah to Hezekiah

00:16:20.000 --> 00:16:22.000
because God answers prayer.

00:16:22.000 --> 00:16:24.000
And he says, number one in verse number five,

00:16:24.000 --> 00:16:26.000
I will heal thee.

00:16:26.000 --> 00:16:27.000
Isn't that precious?

00:16:27.000 --> 00:16:30.000
By the way, it's only God that can do that.

00:16:30.000 --> 00:16:31.000
It's only God that can do that.

00:16:31.000 --> 00:16:33.000
I will heal thee.

00:16:33.000 --> 00:16:34.000
But then God goes a step further.

00:16:34.000 --> 00:16:36.000
He not only says in verse number five there,

00:16:36.000 --> 00:16:38.000
I will heal thee, but he tells him in verse number six,

00:16:38.000 --> 00:16:44.000
I will add unto thy days 15 years.

00:16:44.000 --> 00:16:46.000
I want you to consider just for a moment

00:16:46.000 --> 00:16:49.000
because the thought of what's taking place

00:16:49.000 --> 00:16:51.000
and what's going on in Hezekiah's life,

00:16:51.000 --> 00:16:54.000
he gets the message that he's going to die,

00:16:54.000 --> 00:16:56.000
but then God says, I will heal thee.

00:16:56.000 --> 00:16:57.000
Okay, so I'm going to be healed,

00:16:57.000 --> 00:16:59.000
but for how long, for what's going on?

00:16:59.000 --> 00:17:02.000
And then God says, I'm going to give you 15 more years.

00:17:02.000 --> 00:17:04.000
Again, only God can do that.

00:17:04.000 --> 00:17:06.000
And God is able to do that.

00:17:06.000 --> 00:17:07.000
And God makes that promise.

00:17:07.000 --> 00:17:10.000
And by the way, every promise of God is sure.

00:17:10.000 --> 00:17:11.000
Amen.

00:17:11.000 --> 00:17:13.000
We sang last week, Standing on the Promises,

00:17:13.000 --> 00:17:14.000
and I'm so thankful.

00:17:14.000 --> 00:17:16.000
On Sunday night, we sang that song,

00:17:16.000 --> 00:17:18.000
and I'm so thankful for the promises

00:17:18.000 --> 00:17:20.000
that God has given to us from his word

00:17:20.000 --> 00:17:22.000
and how we need to know those promises

00:17:22.000 --> 00:17:24.000
and we need to stand on those promises,

00:17:24.000 --> 00:17:26.000
knowing that they're absolutely sure.

00:17:26.000 --> 00:17:30.000
And so here, Hezekiah receives this word from the Lord

00:17:31.000 --> 00:17:33.000
in response to his prayer.

00:17:33.000 --> 00:17:37.000
Aren't you, if you think about Hezekiah,

00:17:37.000 --> 00:17:41.000
don't you think he was kind of happy that he prayed?

00:17:41.000 --> 00:17:42.000
You know what I'm saying?

00:17:42.000 --> 00:17:45.000
I mean, what if he hadn't prayed?

00:17:47.000 --> 00:17:49.000
What happens in your life and my life?

00:17:49.000 --> 00:17:51.000
Sometimes we don't pray,

00:17:51.000 --> 00:17:53.000
and then we look around and say, what's going on?

00:17:53.000 --> 00:17:54.000
Why is there this disaster?

00:17:54.000 --> 00:17:55.000
Why is there this mess?

00:17:55.000 --> 00:17:57.000
Why is all there?

00:17:57.000 --> 00:17:59.000
Maybe we should pray.

00:17:59.000 --> 00:18:02.000
And I think Hezekiah was pretty happy that he prayed.

00:18:02.000 --> 00:18:03.000
Amen?

00:18:03.000 --> 00:18:07.000
He gets a promise of healing, a promise of 15 years.

00:18:07.000 --> 00:18:09.000
And we find that in verse 7, it says,

00:18:09.000 --> 00:18:11.000
and Isaiah said, take a lump of figs,

00:18:11.000 --> 00:18:13.000
and they took and laid it on the boil,

00:18:13.000 --> 00:18:16.000
and he, Hezekiah, recovered.

00:18:16.000 --> 00:18:19.000
Now, I want you to notice that we see Hezekiah's prayer,

00:18:19.000 --> 00:18:21.000
we see God's promise,

00:18:21.000 --> 00:18:24.000
but as we finish out the text in verses 8 through 11,

00:18:24.000 --> 00:18:27.000
we're gonna note God's power, God's power.

00:18:27.000 --> 00:18:28.000
I said in the beginning of the message this evening

00:18:28.000 --> 00:18:31.000
that God has as much power today as He's ever had,

00:18:31.000 --> 00:18:34.000
and I'm thankful for that truth.

00:18:34.000 --> 00:18:36.000
And we begin to look here at the message

00:18:36.000 --> 00:18:40.000
that Hezekiah received with regard to the promise from God,

00:18:40.000 --> 00:18:43.000
and Hezekiah is going to request a sign.

00:18:43.000 --> 00:18:46.000
Now, be reminded that the Jews seek for a sign.

00:18:46.000 --> 00:18:49.000
We find that in 1 Corinthians, Paul makes that clear,

00:18:49.000 --> 00:18:53.000
and we note here that Hezekiah is gonna ask for a sign.

00:18:53.000 --> 00:18:55.000
It is interesting to note that the request

00:18:55.000 --> 00:18:59.000
that is made by Hezekiah for a sign is not,

00:18:59.000 --> 00:19:00.000
God doesn't oppose it.

00:19:00.000 --> 00:19:04.000
God doesn't get angry with the request that Hezekiah makes,

00:19:04.000 --> 00:19:06.000
and he makes this request.

00:19:06.000 --> 00:19:09.000
It reminds me a little bit of what we find there

00:19:09.000 --> 00:19:12.000
in the book of Judges, as you think about Gideon,

00:19:12.000 --> 00:19:15.000
and Gideon is given a declaration,

00:19:15.000 --> 00:19:17.000
God meets him and talks to him about victory,

00:19:17.000 --> 00:19:19.000
and what does Gideon do?

00:19:19.000 --> 00:19:21.000
He asks for a sign.

00:19:21.000 --> 00:19:22.000
And what does God do?

00:19:22.000 --> 00:19:25.000
Well, God meets him where he is, and God gives him a sign,

00:19:25.000 --> 00:19:27.000
and Gideon's ready to go, right?

00:19:27.000 --> 00:19:29.000
No, Gideon asks for another sign,

00:19:29.000 --> 00:19:31.000
and God doesn't get angry with him.

00:19:31.000 --> 00:19:32.000
God doesn't get mad at him.

00:19:32.000 --> 00:19:35.000
God's building his faith, and these men,

00:19:35.000 --> 00:19:37.000
as we would think about the Old Testament

00:19:37.000 --> 00:19:39.000
and understand what they had versus what we have,

00:19:39.000 --> 00:19:42.000
we now have the whole canon of Scripture.

00:19:42.000 --> 00:19:45.000
We have the Spirit of God that indwells us as believers,

00:19:45.000 --> 00:19:46.000
and so we don't need the sign.

00:19:46.000 --> 00:19:47.000
We're not looking for a sign,

00:19:47.000 --> 00:19:49.000
but contextually we understand this is the request,

00:19:49.000 --> 00:19:51.000
and God didn't get angry with them,

00:19:51.000 --> 00:19:53.000
and we find that Hezekiah says this in verse number 8,

00:19:53.000 --> 00:19:55.000
and Hezekiah said unto Isaiah,

00:19:55.000 --> 00:19:58.000
What shall be the sign that the Lord will heal me,

00:19:58.000 --> 00:20:00.000
and that I shall go up into the house of the Lord?

00:20:00.000 --> 00:20:02.279
of the Lord the third day.

00:20:02.279 --> 00:20:06.920
And notice Isaiah, according to verse number nine, is going to give these two options.

00:20:06.920 --> 00:20:13.159
In verse number nine it says, and Isaiah said, this sign shalt thou have of the Lord, that

00:20:13.159 --> 00:20:16.719
the Lord will do the thing that he hath spoken.

00:20:16.719 --> 00:20:23.639
And notice the first option, verse nine, shall the shadow go forward ten degrees, or the

00:20:23.639 --> 00:20:28.059
second option, or go back ten degrees.

00:20:28.059 --> 00:20:35.340
So Isaiah gives these options, he makes it clear, this sign shalt thou have of the Lord,

00:20:35.340 --> 00:20:38.180
that the Lord will do the thing that he hath spoken.

00:20:38.180 --> 00:20:39.180
What did God speak?

00:20:39.180 --> 00:20:42.139
Well, I will heal thee, and I'm going to add fifteen years.

00:20:42.139 --> 00:20:47.419
And so we find that the option is laid out, and the Bible says that the two options, the

00:20:47.419 --> 00:20:51.340
shadow would go forward ten degrees, or the shadow would go backward ten degrees.

00:20:51.340 --> 00:20:57.060
Isaiah understood this, Hezekiah understood this, this was something that was very easy

00:20:57.060 --> 00:21:01.939
for them to be able to relate to, and for Hezekiah to be able to process, and the Bible

00:21:01.939 --> 00:21:06.220
says in verse number ten, and we really get the perspective, and this is where we kind

00:21:06.220 --> 00:21:10.400
of come for the whole message this evening with this longing to see God work.

00:21:10.400 --> 00:21:15.860
We see this perspective of Hezekiah, and notice what Hezekiah says.

00:21:15.860 --> 00:21:17.779
Isaiah gives them two options.

00:21:17.779 --> 00:21:25.660
Hezekiah answers and says this, it is a light thing for the shadow to go down ten degrees.

00:21:26.660 --> 00:21:31.779
It's a light thing for the shadow to go down ten degrees.

00:21:31.779 --> 00:21:32.779
Would you agree?

00:21:32.779 --> 00:21:36.819
Yeah, in time, I mean, that's natural.

00:21:36.819 --> 00:21:38.860
That's the normal process.

00:21:38.860 --> 00:21:41.019
So he says it's a light thing.

00:21:41.019 --> 00:21:48.260
We saw that phrase last week as we were studying, where Elisha says to Jehoshaphat, it's a light

00:21:48.260 --> 00:21:49.260
thing.

00:21:49.260 --> 00:21:54.819
It was no problem for God, and so we see here that Hezekiah, as he's processing, he's the

00:21:54.819 --> 00:21:59.540
one that's requested that there be a sign, and Isaiah gives him the two options, and

00:21:59.540 --> 00:22:05.059
he says, well, as he's revealing to us his perspective, well, this would be a light thing.

00:22:05.059 --> 00:22:08.339
This could be just explained away naturally.

00:22:08.339 --> 00:22:11.139
Does that make sense?

00:22:11.139 --> 00:22:15.619
Because naturally, what's going to happen is the shadow's going to go forward ten degrees.

00:22:15.619 --> 00:22:19.580
Did any of you watch the sunset today?

00:22:19.580 --> 00:22:25.059
We sat at dinner, and Joseph sat on the one side of our dinner table, and we're getting

00:22:25.059 --> 00:22:28.979
into the time of, you know, the days are getting a little bit longer, and so we sat down.

00:22:28.979 --> 00:22:32.740
We eat a little earlier on Wednesdays, and so eating earlier, the day's being a little

00:22:32.740 --> 00:22:34.100
bit longer.

00:22:34.100 --> 00:22:37.179
He sat down, and the sun was, bam, right in his eye.

00:22:37.179 --> 00:22:41.179
You know, you just wait just a little while, and guess what's going to happen?

00:22:41.179 --> 00:22:42.179
Sun's going to go down.

00:22:42.179 --> 00:22:43.860
It's not going to be right there anymore, right?

00:22:43.860 --> 00:22:45.179
And we see that.

00:22:45.179 --> 00:22:46.179
That's natural.

00:22:46.179 --> 00:22:49.300
But what he's saying this evening is that when you look at this and you understand the

00:22:49.300 --> 00:22:55.619
perspective that Hezekiah has, he says, well, that could be explained away naturally.

00:22:55.619 --> 00:22:58.259
It's a light thing.

00:22:58.259 --> 00:23:05.860
But notice in verse 10, he says, but let the shadow return backward ten degrees.

00:23:05.860 --> 00:23:08.059
Now that's not normal.

00:23:08.059 --> 00:23:09.940
Amen?

00:23:09.940 --> 00:23:12.259
That's supernatural.

00:23:12.259 --> 00:23:15.220
That's something that only God can do.

00:23:15.259 --> 00:23:16.820
Amen?

00:23:16.820 --> 00:23:22.779
He's the creator and the sustainer, and only God can do this.

00:23:22.779 --> 00:23:29.660
And so we begin to see the perspective of Hezekiah, and he's requesting, he's desiring

00:23:29.660 --> 00:23:36.380
as he's responding to Isaiah that I don't want the easy, the natural, though God would

00:23:36.380 --> 00:23:37.380
do it.

00:23:37.380 --> 00:23:41.860
We saw that in verse number nine, that it was Isaiah that said God will do this thing,

00:23:41.860 --> 00:23:46.300
but he didn't want to have the sign be something that could be explained naturally.

00:23:46.300 --> 00:23:50.300
He wanted it to be supernatural.

00:23:50.300 --> 00:23:58.020
And he says, but let the shadow return backward ten degrees, asking God to do something that

00:23:58.020 --> 00:24:00.979
only God can do.

00:24:00.979 --> 00:24:07.639
Isaiah couldn't do this, Hezekiah couldn't do this, no wise man in Israel could do this.

00:24:07.639 --> 00:24:10.860
It was only God that could do this.

00:24:10.860 --> 00:24:17.220
The Bible says in verse number 11, Isaiah the prophet cried unto the Lord, and he,

00:24:17.220 --> 00:24:25.220
the Lord, brought the shadow ten degrees backward by which it had gone down in the dial of Ahaz.

00:24:25.220 --> 00:24:26.220
That's a miracle.

00:24:26.220 --> 00:24:30.540
That is miraculous that God would do that.

00:24:30.540 --> 00:24:34.700
And we begin to look at this text of Scripture, and we say, okay, so God did it, that God

00:24:34.700 --> 00:24:37.140
demonstrated once again His power.

00:24:37.140 --> 00:24:43.220
He had demonstrated His power to Hezekiah more than once, and we find that as Hezekiah

00:24:43.220 --> 00:24:49.220
now in this particular situation, he cries out to God, he seeks the face of God, and

00:24:49.220 --> 00:24:54.820
then as the Lord answers that prayer and the Lord gives those options, He says, revealing

00:24:54.820 --> 00:24:58.459
to us His perspective, I want to see God work.

00:24:58.459 --> 00:25:02.359
I mentioned this in the very first week that we began studying this little mini-series

00:25:02.359 --> 00:25:04.380
of a longing to see God work.

00:25:04.380 --> 00:25:09.619
We started out in Psalm 119, turn there very quickly, and I want to look at two verses

00:25:09.619 --> 00:25:14.339
that we looked at that first week, but look at Psalm 119 where we started in verse number

00:25:14.339 --> 00:25:21.339
126, and it was really that springboard verse that we used here with regard to this mini-series

00:25:21.339 --> 00:25:23.140
of a longing to see God work.

00:25:23.140 --> 00:25:29.380
I want to see God do something in my life, your life, our church in 2026, and here the

00:25:29.380 --> 00:25:35.859
psalmist says in Psalm 119, 126, it is time for thee, Lord, to work, for they have made

00:25:35.859 --> 00:25:38.459
void thy law.

00:25:38.459 --> 00:25:40.779
And I love what the psalmist prays.

00:25:40.779 --> 00:25:45.339
I love the perspective of the psalmist, and again, as I mentioned that very first week,

00:25:45.339 --> 00:25:46.339
it wasn't a demand.

00:25:46.339 --> 00:25:49.660
We can't demand that God works.

00:25:49.660 --> 00:25:51.440
We simply make the request.

00:25:51.440 --> 00:25:53.779
We simply seek His face.

00:25:53.779 --> 00:26:03.260
We earnestly and fervently pray, and we desire, we long to see God do what only God can do.

00:26:03.260 --> 00:26:09.140
There's times in which you can look at relationships in life, and there's a problem in a relationship,

00:26:09.140 --> 00:26:11.140
and sometimes I'm going to fix that person.

00:26:11.140 --> 00:26:15.640
No, let God do what only God can do.

00:26:15.640 --> 00:26:20.940
And we can look at so many different arenas of life and begin to think about needing to

00:26:20.940 --> 00:26:27.839
see the Lord work, and obviously in our society as we continue to live in these perilous days

00:26:27.839 --> 00:26:34.739
and we see evil men and seducers maxing worse and worse, and we begin to see even just more

00:26:34.739 --> 00:26:40.440
open sinfulness and wickedness and all that's taking place, and we say, Lord, they've made

00:26:40.440 --> 00:26:42.119
void thy law.

00:26:42.119 --> 00:26:49.940
We live in a society that they've just disregarded the truth, the truth that God has given to us.

00:26:49.940 --> 00:26:53.799
We need to see God work.

00:26:53.799 --> 00:26:59.019
My fancy arguments and your fancy arguments, they're not going to cut it.

00:26:59.019 --> 00:27:01.459
We need the power of God.

00:27:01.459 --> 00:27:03.380
We need what only God can do.

00:27:03.380 --> 00:27:07.820
I can't change a heart, and neither can you, but God can.

00:27:07.820 --> 00:27:08.820
Amen?

00:27:08.820 --> 00:27:11.140
God is able.

00:27:11.140 --> 00:27:15.420
And the reality is that we can't, you know, you might be able to for a little while, you

00:27:15.420 --> 00:27:19.739
might be able to have some influence over someone and get them to behave and act a certain

00:27:19.739 --> 00:27:27.179
way, but how much better to have God work in their lives and God do something in and

00:27:27.179 --> 00:27:28.179
through their lives?

00:27:28.179 --> 00:27:32.339
And we find that the other text of Scripture that we looked at on that first week, look

00:27:32.339 --> 00:27:37.500
back at Psalm 109, and I just want to remind you of what the psalmist said in Psalm 109,

00:27:37.500 --> 00:27:41.660
and we relate it to what we're looking at here this evening with Hezekiah, and he says

00:27:41.660 --> 00:27:47.540
it's a light thing if the shadow were to go forward ten degrees, but no, if the shadow

00:27:47.579 --> 00:27:50.260
to go backward ten degrees, that is a supernatural.

00:27:50.260 --> 00:27:54.940
He doesn't say in the text that it's a hard thing, a difficult thing, a supernatural thing,

00:27:54.940 --> 00:27:58.540
but he does say that it's a light thing for the shadow to go forward ten degrees, and

00:27:58.540 --> 00:28:03.260
he makes the request that it go backward ten degrees, and I believe that it would not be

00:28:03.260 --> 00:28:09.660
a stretch for us to understand the perspective and the logic of Hezekiah to say that's not

00:28:09.660 --> 00:28:10.739
natural.

00:28:10.739 --> 00:28:12.579
That requires God.

00:28:12.579 --> 00:28:17.779
And in Psalm 109, in verse number 27, the Bible says that they may know that this is

00:28:17.779 --> 00:28:23.899
thy hand, that thou, Lord, hast done it.

00:28:23.899 --> 00:28:27.820
Let me ask you a question.

00:28:27.820 --> 00:28:35.780
Was it just Hezekiah and Isaiah that experienced ten degrees backwards?

00:28:35.780 --> 00:28:37.940
Nope.

00:28:37.940 --> 00:28:39.419
Could you imagine being there?

00:28:40.299 --> 00:28:42.820
What would you think?

00:28:42.820 --> 00:28:43.820
This is...

00:28:43.820 --> 00:28:44.820
What's up?

00:28:44.820 --> 00:28:45.820
Something's weird.

00:28:45.820 --> 00:28:46.820
What's going on?

00:28:46.820 --> 00:28:49.020
Am I right?

00:28:49.020 --> 00:29:00.059
Because this is not normal, and God did something that could only be explained as God did it.

00:29:00.859 --> 00:29:09.580
And it was a sign, yes, for Hezekiah, confirming the promise that God gave to Hezekiah, yes.

00:29:09.580 --> 00:29:10.979
But why do we go here?

00:29:10.979 --> 00:29:17.500
Why is it that the Lord has led me to go to this passage and for us to study this evening,

00:29:17.500 --> 00:29:20.700
this thought with regard to Hezekiah and this historical event?

00:29:20.700 --> 00:29:23.979
Okay, great, that happened in his life, and so what does that mean for us?

00:29:23.979 --> 00:29:28.700
Well, let me ask you this evening as we would examine our own lives, and we would begin

00:29:28.700 --> 00:29:31.219
to think about that longing to see God work.

00:29:31.219 --> 00:29:37.219
First of all, does it encourage you when you see things like this to know the power of

00:29:37.219 --> 00:29:38.580
God?

00:29:38.580 --> 00:29:41.659
Because the Bible says, so then faith cometh by hearing, and hearing by the word of God.

00:29:41.659 --> 00:29:43.940
And so my faith is increased.

00:29:43.940 --> 00:29:50.340
My faith is growing as I read the Scriptures and as God proves His power and He demonstrates

00:29:50.340 --> 00:29:51.340
His power.

00:29:51.340 --> 00:29:57.739
Man, that encourages me, and that causes me to rejoice, not only in what God did for Hezekiah,

00:29:57.739 --> 00:30:00.539
but understanding that His God is my God.

00:30:00.539 --> 00:30:08.139
God. And he's got as much power today as he did then. And then I begin to think about this. What

00:30:08.139 --> 00:30:15.979
is it in your life and in my life that is kind of the hard thing? Again, and I know I'm kind of

00:30:15.979 --> 00:30:20.219
repeating myself, but I'm trying to bring this package all together. In the very first week,

00:30:20.219 --> 00:30:25.899
we talked about how that sometimes in our society and unfortunately even in our churches,

00:30:25.899 --> 00:30:34.459
we have learned how to manufacture results. There's a time, and we try to be very careful

00:30:34.459 --> 00:30:41.259
with this, but there are times in which there are very emotional type appeals that are given

00:30:41.259 --> 00:30:47.739
and people are making emotional decisions. And something that I've learned about emotional

00:30:47.739 --> 00:30:53.419
decisions is that oftentimes they don't endure. They don't last. Why? Because your emotions are

00:30:53.419 --> 00:30:59.099
going to change. Your feelings are going to change. It's not based on feeling. When we make decisions,

00:30:59.099 --> 00:31:03.419
those decisions need to be based upon something that's unchanging, and that's God's Word.

00:31:04.139 --> 00:31:09.739
Not upon my feelings, not upon my emotions. And there are people that have learned how to

00:31:09.739 --> 00:31:15.659
really work a crowd, if I could use that phraseology, and they've been able to manufacture

00:31:15.659 --> 00:31:20.699
types of responses and results and so on and so forth. I'm not looking for that.

00:31:21.659 --> 00:31:27.579
I'm looking for God to work. I'm longing to see God do what only God can do.

00:31:28.619 --> 00:31:34.379
And that's what we see with Hezekiah. He says to Isaiah, now imagine again, I want a sign.

00:31:35.739 --> 00:31:41.979
What sign is God going to give me? Well, here's two options. Okay, well, that one's a light thing,

00:31:43.019 --> 00:31:48.779
could be explained away naturally. So let's go with this one because I know God, and I know God

00:31:49.339 --> 00:31:57.419
can do that. Isn't that precious? And as we look at our lives, I don't want anyone to tell me. You

00:31:57.419 --> 00:32:05.099
don't need to tell anyone else. But in your life and in my life, what are we seeking? What are we

00:32:05.099 --> 00:32:13.499
praying that is something that only God can do? That we're not trying to manipulate and manufacture

00:32:14.219 --> 00:32:21.499
results and trying to... No, no, no. We just can sit back and say, God did it. God did it.

00:32:22.059 --> 00:32:28.619
There's no other way to explain it. They could not explain the shadow going back 10 degrees

00:32:29.659 --> 00:32:36.539
except for to simply say, God did it. And I love that. And that's what I want to see God do. Let's

00:32:36.539 --> 00:32:41.979
pray. Father, we love you. We thank you so much for loving us. We thank you for the privilege

00:32:41.979 --> 00:32:47.419
of being your children. Thank you for the privilege of prayer. And God, I pray that you

00:32:47.419 --> 00:32:55.019
would help us to be people of prayer. God, we would pray immediately as we see in the text with

00:32:55.019 --> 00:33:00.939
Hezekiah, that we would pray fervently as we see in the text with Hezekiah. Lord, I pray that you

00:33:00.939 --> 00:33:07.659
would help us to seek you early. Lord, that you would hear our voice, that we would regularly be

00:33:07.659 --> 00:33:16.059
in your presence. Thank you for your promises. The reminder that you hear and that you see,

00:33:16.059 --> 00:33:22.219
Lord, it encourages us. It comforts us. But to see how you gave promises to Hezekiah, Lord,

00:33:22.219 --> 00:33:30.299
we thank you for that answer. We thank you for just providing Hezekiah with a timely answer

00:33:30.299 --> 00:33:36.539
with regard to the situation. And then we see your power. God, how we long to see you work.

00:33:39.339 --> 00:33:45.099
God, I pray that you would help us as individual believers and corporately as a church

00:33:46.059 --> 00:33:51.659
to truly long to see you work. God, to see you do the impossible

00:33:52.539 --> 00:33:58.939
so that you would receive the glory. Thank you for the opportunity that we have on Wednesday

00:33:58.939 --> 00:34:06.379
evening to not only study your word, but to pray together, to come together as a church family and

00:34:06.379 --> 00:34:12.459
to enter into corporate prayer, intercessory prayer. Lord, we thank you for the privilege.

00:34:12.459 --> 00:34:18.219
And I pray that you would bless the remainder of our time this evening, Lord, that you would

00:34:18.219 --> 00:34:25.259
be honored and glorified. And we'll thank you for it. In Christ's name we pray. Amen.

